<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA4FFD83AF5088044DAB8FE" box="[942,1012,950,977]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Goiás</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FFA4FFD839E608EC438EBF37" blockId="42.[136,1452,950,1444]" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA4FFD839E608EC4690B8DB" bold="true" box="[189,446,986,1012]" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Nomenclatural notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FFA4FFD8388108EC44EFB8DB" authorityName="Bentham" authorityYear="1876" box="[474,961,986,1013]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="42" pageNumber="269" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="polyphyllum" variety="villosum">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA4FFD8388108EC4402B8DB" box="[474,812,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Stryphnodendron polyphyllum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="91843240FFA4FFD83A3908EC44EFB8DB" box="[866,961,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">villosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="C76193A3FFA4FFD83DD608EC426DB8DA" author="Bentham, G." box="[1165,1347,986,1013]" pageId="42" pageNumber="269" pagination="257 - 502" refId="ref41697" refString="Bentham, G. (1876) Leguminosae II et III. Mimoseae. In: Martius, C. F. P. (Ed.) Flora brasiliensis. v. 15, pars 2. Lipsiae apud Frid. Fleishcer in Comm., Monachii, pp. 257 - 502." type="book chapter" year="1876">Bentham (1876)</bibRefCitation>
based on 
<specimenCount id="B5F625DBFFA4FFD839D308C94630BF36" box="[136,286,1023,1049]" pageId="42" pageNumber="269" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">two syntypes</specimenCount>
, 
<emphasis id="91843240FFA4FFD8387208C84697BF37" box="[297,441,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Weddel 2936</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="91843240FFA4FFD838AB08C845A0BF37" box="[496,654,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Burchell 5600</emphasis>
. The latter specimen was selected as 
<typeStatus id="7C4B50F0FFA4FFD83D6908C843B2BF37" box="[1074,1180,1022,1048]" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FFA4FFD839E60F1443A4BFE2" pageId="42" pageNumber="269" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FFA4FFD839E60F1444DDBF87" blockId="42.[136,1452,950,1444]" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA4FFD839E60F1446C7BF13" bold="true" box="[189,489,1058,1084]" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FFA4FFD83B5E0F1444D5BF13" authorityName="Scalon" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Bentham" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[517,1019,1058,1085]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="42" pageNumber="269" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="rotundifolium" variety="villosum">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA4FFD83B5E0F14444BBF13" box="[517,869,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Stryphnodendron rotundifolium</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="91843240FFA4FFD83AC70F1444D5BF13" box="[924,1019,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">villosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in Central 
<collectingCountry id="DBE7AEC2FFA4FFD83C3B0F144289BF13" box="[1376,1447,1058,1084]" name="Brazil" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, where it occurs mainly in cerrados 
<emphasis id="91843240FFA4FFD83B4E0F71458DBF4F" box="[533,675,1095,1120]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">sensu stricto</emphasis>
of 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA4FFD83B920F704423BF4F" box="[713,781,1094,1120]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Goiás</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA4FFD83A420F7044E5BF4F" box="[793,971,1094,1120]" country="Brazil" name="Distrito Federal" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Federal District</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA4FFD83A8C0F704335BF4F" box="[983,1051,1094,1120]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA4FFD83D7C0F7043B5BF4F" box="[1063,1179,1094,1120]" country="Brazil" name="Maranhao" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Maranhão</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA4FFD83DFC0F714216BF4F" box="[1191,1336,1094,1121]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA4FFD83C2B0F71460BBFAB" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Mato Grosso do Sul</collectingRegion>
states. This taxon is less frequently found in cerradão, campos and rarely in campos rupestres of Central 
<collectingCountry id="DBE7AEC2FFA4FFD839D30FB847FEBF87" box="[136,208,1166,1192]" name="Brazil" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The registers of this species in 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA4FFD83B6E0FB845CEBF86" box="[565,736,1166,1193]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">São Paulo state</collectingRegion>
are all cultivated plants.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FFA4FFD839E60F8443A4BFE2" blockId="42.[136,1452,950,1444]" box="[189,1162,1202,1229]" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA4FFD839E60F844649BFE3" bold="true" box="[189,359,1202,1228]" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Conservation:</emphasis>
—Least Concern (LC) [AOO= 
<quantity id="640843B7FFA4FFD83BE50F844468BFE3" box="[702,838,1202,1228]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.72" pageId="42" pageNumber="269" unit="km" value="172.0">172.000 km</quantity>
<superScript id="5485431AFFA4FFD83A1E0F844463BFEF" attach="left" box="[837,845,1202,1216]" fontSize="6" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">2</superScript>
, EOO= 
<quantity id="640843B7FFA4FFD83AFF0F84435FBFE3" box="[932,1137,1202,1228]" metricMagnitude="9" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.222428394" pageId="42" pageNumber="269" unit="km" value="1222428.394">1,222,428.394 km</quantity>
<superScript id="5485431AFFA4FFD83D2A0F844357BFEF" attach="left" box="[1137,1145,1202,1216]" fontSize="6" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">2</superScript>
].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FFA4FFD839E60FE044E8BE3A" pageId="42" pageNumber="269" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FFA4FFD839E60FE044E8BE3A" blockId="42.[136,1452,950,1444]" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA4FFD839E60FE0466DBFDF" bold="true" box="[189,323,1238,1264]" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Phenology:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FFA4FFD838040FE14585BFDF" authorityName="Scalon" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Bentham" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[351,683,1238,1265]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="42" pageNumber="269" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="rotundifolium" variety="villosum">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA4FFD838040FE14643BFDE" box="[351,365,1239,1265]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="91843240FFA4FFD838200FE0453ABFDF" box="[379,532,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">rotundifolium</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="91843240FFA4FFD83B170FE04585BFDF" box="[588,683,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">villosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected with flowers throughout the year (except March, June and September) and with fruits from April to November (except October).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
